<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="How_to_install_and_test_xrootd_g"></a> How to install and test xrootd-gridftp rpm </span></h2>
<p /> <ol>
<li> Obtain hostcertificate and place it <code><b>/etc/grid-security/hostcert.pem</b></code>,  <code><b>/etc/grid-security/hostkey.pem</b></code> 
</li> <li> Create <code><b>/etc/yum.repos.d/vdt.repo</b></code> <pre class="rootscreen">
[vdt-development]
name = VDT RPM repository - development versions for Redhat Enterprise Linux 5 and compatible
baseurl = http://vdt.cs.wisc.edu/native/rpm/development/rh5/$basearch
gpgcheck = 0
enabled = 1
<font color="#008000">#### skip that if you already have CAs certificate installed from some other source</font>
[vdt-ca-certs]
name=VDT CA Certificates
baseurl=http://vdt.cs.wisc.edu/vdt_rpms/vdt-ca-certs
gpgcheck=0
enabled=1
</pre>
</li> <li> Install xrootd-grdftp and related packages:<pre class="rootscreen">
$ yum install vdt-ca-certs #<font color="#008000">execute this command only if you want CA certificates from VDT</font>

$ yum install xrootd-dsi
....
=======================================================================================================================================================================
 Package                                         Arch                           Version                                  Repository                               Size
=======================================================================================================================================================================
Installing:
 xrootd-dsi                                     x86_64                        3.0.4-1                                  vdt-development                         19 k
Installing for dependencies:
 globus-base-data-server                        x86_64                        4.0.8-7                                  vdt-development                        498 k
 globus-base-essentials                         x86_64                        4.0.8-7                                  vdt-development                         13 M
 gpt                                            x86_64                        3.2-3.gt408.1                            vdt-development                        1.3 M
 vdt-compat                                     noarch                        2.0.0.22-5                               vdt-development                        4.0 k
 xrootd-client                                  x86_64                        1:3.0.4-0.rc1.xu                         vdt-development                        1.5 M
 xrootd-libs                                    x86_64                        1:3.0.4-0.rc1.xu                         vdt-development                        1.9 M


=======================================================================================================================================================================
</pre>
</li> <li> If you want to use <code><b>grid-mapfile</b></code> for authorization you have to manually create it under <code><b>/etc/grid-security</b></code>, for example:<pre class="file">"/DC=org/DC=doegrids/OU=People/CN=Tanya Levshina 508821" fnalgrid</pre> If you want to use GUMS you will need to install additional package:<pre class="rootscreen">yum install prima</pre> and then modify information related to your GUMS server in <code><b>prima-authz.conf</b></code> under <code><b>/etc/grid-security</b></code>. <ul>
<li> <code><b>/etc/grid-security/prima-authz.conf</b></code>:<pre class="file">....

# This is the identity mapping server, it performs a mapping based on the gridmap file on the service host
imsContact https://<font color="#ff0000">!!HOSTNAME!!</font>:8443/gums/services/GUMSAuthorizationServicePort
xacmlContact https://<font color="#ff0000">!!HOSTNAME!!</font>:8443/gums/services/GUMSXACMLAuthorizationServicePort

</pre> Where you have to replace <font color="#ff0000">!!HOSTNAME!!</font> with FQDN of your GUMS server, if your GUMS server is running on the port other then 8443 you have to change it as well.
</li></ul> 
</li></ol> 
<p /> <ol>
<li> Modify  <code><b>xrootd-gsiftp.sh</b></code> in <code><b>/opt/vdt/setup.d</b></code> <pre class="file">
# This file must not be world-writable, and must be owned by root

# You need to edit XROOTD_VMP if XROOTD_HOST, XROOTD_MOUNT_POINT
# or XROOTD_REDIRECTOR_STORAGEPATH are present in the line below.
export XROOTD_VMP="<font color="#ff0000">redirector_node</font>:1094:<font color="#ff0000">/local_mount_point</font>=<font color="#ff0000">/storage_path</font>"
# Replace redirector_node and storage_path with the xrootd redirector
# ie. root://redirector_node:1094/storage_path
# This will map to /local_mount_point on the local machine / gridftp server


# You almost certainly should not edit XROOTDLIB or LD_PRELOAD
# unless you are running i386 or 32 bit arch, in which case
# XROOTDLIB should be "/usr/lib"
export XROOTDLIB=/usr/lib64
export LD_PRELOAD=$XROOTDLIB/libXrdPosixPreload.so
</pre> Replace <font color="#ff0000">redirector_node</font> with the name of your redirector host, <font color="#ff0000">local_mount_point</font> with a virtual mount point (e.g "/atlas") and <font color="#ff0000">/storage_path</font> with your redirector storage_path
</li> <li> Start/stop service<pre class="rootscreen"> 
$ service  globus-gridftp-server  start
Starting GridFTP server...                                 <font color="#008000">[  OK  ]</font>
$ service  globus-gridftp-server  stop
</pre>
</li> <li> Tests gridftp/xrootd from the node where OSG client is installed or globus commands are available: <ul>
<li> login on the node as non-root user
</li> <li> Make sure that <code><b>grid-proxy-init</b></code>, <code><b>globus-url-copy</b></code> is in your path.
</li> <li> obtain grid proxy, e.g:<pre class="screen">
grid-proxy-init 
Your identity: /DC=org/DC=doegrids/OU=People/CN=Tanya Levshina 508821
Enter GRID pass phrase for this identity:
Creating proxy ...................................... Done
Your proxy is valid until: Thu Apr 28 04:07:30 2011</pre> 
</li> <li> Check that you can access gridftp host<pre class="screen"> 
$ uberftp <font color="#ff0000">gridftp_server</font>
220 fermicloud015.fnal.gov GridFTP Server 2.8 (gcc64dbg, 1217607445-63) ['VDT patched' 4.0.8] ready.
230 User tlevshin logged in.

UberFTP> ls /tmp
-rw-------   1     root     root          115 Apr  5 10:14    test
drwx------   2     root     root         4096 Apr  5 09:38 blah
....
</pre>
</li> <li> Test it with globus-url-copy:<pre class="screen"> 
$ globus-url-copy file:///bin/sh gsiftp://<font color="#ff0000">gridftp-server</font>:2811//<font color="#ff0000">mount_point</font>/test
</pre>
</li></ul> 
</li></ol> 
<p />
<p />
-- <a href="/bin/view/Main/TanyaLevshina" class="twikiLink">TanyaLevshina</a> - 05 Apr 2011</div><!-- /patternTopic-->
